mcqs.question:
What will be the output of the following code?
int x = 10;
int *ptr = &x;
printf("%d", *ptr);

What is the output?
int arr[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
int *p = arr;
printf("%d", *(p+2));

What is the output?
int a = 5;
int *p = &a;
int **pp = &p;
printf("%d", **pp);

What will be printed?
char str[] = "Hello";
char *p = str;
printf("%c", *p++);

What is the output?
int arr[3] = {10, 20, 30};
int *ptr = arr;
printf("%d %d", *(ptr+1), *(arr+2));

What will be the output?
int x = 5;
int *p = &x;
printf("%p %p", &x, p);
